The paper deals with lower bounds for depth-4 circuits, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of combinatorial designs and matrices suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DS), while the comparison with determinantal complexity points towards information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves some geometric arguments related to polynomial interpolation, which could fall under computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for polynomial regression could connect to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
